<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="161" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1717,2032]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
This group is defined by the peculiar shape of everted endophallus and paramera strongly narrowing in the distal half (
<figureCitation box="[246,341,1789,1816]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1869,1894]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,208,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Pygopleurus anemoninus (Brullé, 1832), habitus and genitalia. 18, male (Achaia, Kalogria); 19, male (Elis, Keramidia); 20, female (Achaia, Kalogria); 21, female (Elis, Keramidia); 22, left paramere in lateral and dorsal view (Messenia, Messini); 23, everted endophallus in left lateral view (Messenia, Messini); 24, left genital sclerites of female (Achaia, Araxos)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3458850/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Figs. 22</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[352,383,1790,1816]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–31" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1869,1894]" captionTargetBox="[163,1408,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–31. Pygopleurus pseudopsilotrichius (Petrovitz, 1958), habitus and genitalia. 25, male (Lakonia, Gorani); 26, male (Arcadia, Karitena); 27, female (Lakonia, Chanià); 28, female (Lakonia, Gorani); 29, left paramere in lateral and dorsal view (Laconia, Chanià); 30, everted endophallus in left lateral view (Laconia, Chanià); 31, left genital sclerites of female (Laconia, Dafni)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3458852/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">29</figureCitation>
), very distinct from other 
<taxonomicName box="[678,820,1789,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Pygopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[678,820,1789,1815]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Pygopleurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and suggestive of the monophyly of the group, and by the clypeus lacking a medial carina in both sexes, a condition exclusive to this group within the Greek fauna. Other non-exclusive characters are: elytra unicolored, long, raised setation of elytra with black setae commonly present at least in the basal area, rarely all setae light-colored (observed in females only); setation evidently denser in the inner two-thirds of elytra, scarce or absent in the external third; elytral apex rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="161" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1717,2032]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
The group includes two species from 
<collectingCountry box="[615,694,1970,1996]" name="Greece" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Greece</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brulle" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[710,872,1970,1995]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Pygopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anemoninus">
<emphasis box="[710,872,1970,1995]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">P. anemoninus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Petrovitz" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[925,1172,1969,1995]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Pygopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudopsilotrichius">
<emphasis box="[925,1172,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">P. pseudopsilotrichius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and one from 
<collectingCountry box="[1340,1436,1969,1995]" name="Turkey" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authority="(Petrovitz, 1962))" authorityName="" authorityYear="1962" baseAuthorityName="Petrovitz" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[161,461,2005,2032]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Pygopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareli">
<emphasis box="[161,252,2005,2031]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">P. kareli</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Petrovitz, R." box="[267,443,2005,2032]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" pagination="107 - 124" refId="ref30865" refString="Petrovitz, R. (1962) Neue und interessante Scarabaeidae aus dem vorderen Orienten. I. Teil. Reichenbachia, 1 (15), 107 - 124." type="journal article" year="1962">Petrovitz, 1962</bibRefCitation>
))
</taxonomicName>
, whose everted endophallus is pictured in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bollino, M. &amp; Ruzzante, G." box="[936,1245,2005,2032]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" pagination="69 - 74" refId="ref29780" refString="Bollino, M. &amp; Ruzzante, G. (2015) Corological notes on some species of Pygopleurus (Coleoptera: Glaphyridae) from the Greek Island of Lesbos. Munis Entomology and Zoology, 10 (1), 69 - 74." type="journal article" year="2015">Bollino &amp; Ruzzante (2015)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
